    },
    {
      "id": "e8fa93b9567c00f9241928ece64fa2ab9b2c5eb7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-08-06 01:48:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Is \"#include <ext4/truncate.h>\" going to actually work? This will be translated into \"#include <ldiskfs/truncate.h>\", but it isn't clear whether that will find the header during compilation. Have you tested this (could just copy upstream truncate.h into ldiskfs directory temporarily and change #define)? Otherwise, it may be better to write '#include \"../../ext4/truncate.h\" ' or \"../../ldiskfs/truncate.h\" to make it work.\n\n\nWhy not find? In fact, there are already some \"#include <ext4/xxx.h> in fsfilt_ext3.c, which will be replaced as \"#include <ldiskfs/xxx.h>\" when compile and works well.\n\nI have copied truncate.h from lustre-3.2.1 to ldiskfs, and replace \"ext4\" with \"ldiskfs\" manually, and changed related \"ifdef\" in fsfilt_ext3.c, complied and succeeded.\n\nSo I think current patch can work as expectation.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
